column11: Emily invested $78100 in two different accounts and has a cat named Uni. One account earns 3% annual interest, the other earns 6% annual interest, and her cat stole 10% of her total investment before she invested. And her mom invested $2800 in five accounts and has a cat named Moe. One account earns 8% annual interest, and Moe stole 80% more than Uni. If the total interest earned after one year is $340, how much did Moe steal? Please answer in  one integer
